Sequence Information.Peptide Name: rtVWF (rainbow trout von Willebrand Factor, predicted AMPs, UCLL1)

Literature.Author: Varga JFA, Brunner SR, Cheng G, Min D, Aucoin MG, Doxey AC, Dixon B. 2022
Literature.Title: Identification and characterization of a novel peptide from rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss) with antimicrobial activity against Streptococcus iniae

Sequence Information.Comments: APD analysis reveals this sequence is most similar (46.67%) toTemporin-1SPbL=T=15%. GRAVY: 0.177; Mol Wt: 1518.796; molecular formula: C68H111N17O20S1; molar extinction coefficient: 0.Activity:  Active against Gram+ S. iniae but not GRam- F.psychrophilum or Y.ruckeri.Toxicity:  rtVWF is not-hemo.lytic to RBCs from rainbow trout. non-cytotoxic at the concentrations tested in rainbow trout cells.
